When a user exceeds their query limit, API requests return an error response indicating insufficient credits. The response will look like this:

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS",
    "message": "Need 5000 credits, have 5000"
  }
}
``` 

This means the user has reached their monthly query limit and cannot make additional requests until the limit resets.

